ATTACHMENT ID: 12850037 - PreCommit-HIVE-Build, Committed to 2.2.0, and thanks [~pxiong] for review., [~alex.behm] The patch provided here is mainly to fix some Hive alter table DDLs and ensure them not to drop table stats accidentally. There was not much change in HMS. However, HIVE-12730 introduced some new HMS APIs (e.g. void alter_table_with_environmentContext) which allow user to pass a flag StatsSetupConst.DO_NOT_UPDATE_STATS true to HMS and indicate it not to update the stats. These new APIs could probably be used in Impala. BTW, the StatsSetupConst.STATS_GENERATED_VIA_STATS_TASK has been dropped in HIVE-12730., Thanks for the info, [~ctang.ma]! I agree the alter_table_with_environmentContext() seems useful. 

Is my understanding correct that even after your patch the HMS alter_table() will drop stats in some cases?, Yes, unfortunately, [~alex.behm]. But if you pass StatsSetupConst.DO_NOT_UPDATE_STATS TRUE as a table parameter, the alter_table should not drop the stats as well I think., Thanks, [~ctang.ma]. I've already added a workaround to Impala, but not using StatsSetupConst.DO_NOT_UPDATE_STATS because sometimes we do want to update stats (e.g. compute stats).
See: http://gerrit.cloudera.org:8080/5731, the STATS_GENERATED_VIA_STATS_TASK used in your workaround has been removed in HIVE-12730, you may run into some issues when you upgrade to use Hive 2.1., [~ctang.ma], am I understanding correctly that there is no interest in fixing this issue on the Metastore side? I understand that all clients can pass DO_NOT_UPDATE_STATS.]